Dammam 7 to Work on $1 Billion Acrylic Acid Plant, Watan Says

-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 
2011-02-15T10:44:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/dammam-7-to-work-on-1-billion-acrylic-acid-plant-watan-says.html
Saudi Arabia’s Dammam 7
Petrochemical Co. will start building a $1 billion factory in
the second quarter to make acrylic acid and acrylates,  Saudi
Arabia ’s al-Watan reported.  The new plant at the Persian Gulf port of Jubail is due to
begin operating on a trial basis in the first half of 2014, the
newspaper said today, citing the company’s President Ibrahim
Bahairi. The facility will increase global production of butanol
and acrylic acid by 5 percent, according to the report. The
facility will be built by  China ’s Shanghai Huayi Group Co., it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maher Chmaytelli in Dubai at 
